{
  "texts": [
    "Adoption of these tools holds promise to further protect and advance ethical and societal values, especially where traditional regulatory responses are insufficient.",
    "Regulatory sandboxing.",
    "Participants suggested regulatory sandboxing as a system to further collaboration and learning between regulators and innovators in contexts where innovation is highly novel, and the applicability of existing laws and regulatory responses is uncertain.",
    "Before launching novel technologies, regulatory sandboxing allows innovators to test their innovation under close regulatory supervision.",
    "Regulators can simultaneously experiment with novel regulatory approaches to such innovation."
  ]
}